                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>An incomplete block of limestone, damaged on the left, right, below and at the rear; only the front face and upper surface are preserved. The nature of the upper surface suggests that at least one more block originally stood on top of this one; at least one deliberately cut indentation is visible on the upper surface, presumably for the joining of blocks.</p>
